  "prompt": "How do I get person online status when he is on whatsapp call?",
  "response": "To determine a person's online status while they are on a WhatsApp call, you'll need to consider a few methods:\n\n1. WhatsApp Native Method:\n- When someone is on a call, their status will typically show as \"Busy\" or \"On call\"\n- Look at their profile status or last seen\n\n2. WhatsApp Web/Desktop Indicators:\n- Sometimes the online/offline indicators might still work\n- Check their profile on WhatsApp Web or Desktop\n\n3. Third-Party Apps/Tools:\n- Some third-party tracking apps claim to provide detailed status information\n- Be cautious, as these might violate WhatsApp's terms of service\n\n4. Programming Approaches (for developers):\n- WhatsApp Web API\n- WhatsApp Business API\n- Custom parsing of WhatsApp status\n\nTechnical Considerations:\n- WhatsApp doesn't provide direct public API for real-time status\n- Status detection can be complex and may violate privacy policies\n- Accuracy depends on various factors\n\nRecommended Ethical Approach:\n- Respect user privacy\n- Use built-in WhatsApp status indicators\n- Avoid invasive tracking methods\n\nNote: Precise online status during calls isn't consistently available due to privacy protections.",
